The House of Representatives has approved N4 trillion for subsidy on Premium Motor Spirit (PMS). Recall that President Muhammadu Buhari requested a revision of the 2021 fiscal framework from N442 billion to N4 trillion in the letter titled “Submission of the Revised 2022 Fiscal Framework” which was dated April 5, 2022. The House of Representatives also approved a cut in the provision for Federally Funded upstream projects being implemented by the federal government by about N200 billion from N352.80 billion. A reduction in crude oil production quota from 1.8million barrels per day to 1.6 million barrels per day and a 73 dollar oil price benchmark was also approved by the House.